   [bullet icon] Calendar
   [bullet icon] Research
   [bullet icon] News Releases

                                  Headlines

   16 Nov 01
   FSL's Supercomputer Supports Wide Range of Projects
   The Jet Allocation Committee met recently and awarded time on Jet to a
   broad range of projects.

   9 Nov 01
   FSL to share observations and observation-handling software
   A new project at FSL, the Meteorological Assimilation Data Ingest
   System (MADIS), is making value-added, quality-controlled data freely
   available from FSL's Central Facility. Software to read the
   observations is also provided.

   18 Oct 01
   FSL's GPS-Met Data to Aid Forecasters During Winter Olympics
   Atmospheric water vapor information observed by the FSL-developed
   GPS-met system will support weather forecasting for the XIX Olympic
   Winter Games in Utah.

   Another Award for the Boss
   FSL Director A.E. "Sandy" MacDonald was named a Meritorious
   Presidential Rank Award winner by President George W. Bush. He was
   presented the award on 15 October. This is the second such award for
   Sandy, having been named a Distinguished Executive in 1997.

   3 Oct 01
   Profiler Network Backs National Readiness
   The NOAA Profiler Network, operated by FSL's Demonstration Division,
   provides up to date information that is a valuable national asset in
   the event of the release of harmful substances in the atmosphere.

   20 Sep 01
   Supercomputer Upgrade
   A recent upgrade to FSL's supercomputer has more than doubled its
   processing power.

   29 Aug 01
   Verification Goes Real Time
   FSL's Aviation Division is working with the National Weather Service's
   Aviation Weather Center on real-time verification of aviation weather
   advisories.

   13 Aug 01
   Air Force Space Launch Operations Getting a Boost from FSL
   Under an agreement with Lockheed Martin, FSL is providing enhancements
   to the National Weather Service interactive weather display system to
   support Air Force space operations at the Western Range launch
   facility.

   23 Jul 2001
   FSL Employees Win Research Awards
   Congratulations to the following FSL recipients of CIRA Research
   Initiative Awards:

     Dan Schaffer of the Aviation Division's Advanced Computing Branch,
     Amenda Stanley of the Facility Division, and
     the FX-Net Team of Renate Br√ºmmer, Sean Madine, Ning Wang, Evan
     Polster, and John Pyle.

   10 Jul 2001
   FSL Workshop Investigates a Next Generation Weather Observing System
   FSL recently hosted leaders in the field of Global Positioning System
   (GPS) measurement science to discuss a new and potentially significant
   way to use GPS for atmospheric remote sensing.

   09 Jul 2001
   Hail to the Chief
   FCW.COM (Federal Computer Week), the government information technology
   on-line resource and a product of the FCW Government Technology Group,
   has recently presented one of its 2001 Federal 100 Awards to FSL's
   Sandy MacDonald.

